<item>
            <title>[LU-12157] lfs_migrate -v output format is not well-formed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12157</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The output from &quot;lfs_migrate -v&quot; is not well formed when migrating links or special files.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/mnt/testfs/l0: /mnt/testfs/l0: done
\n\r[K/mnt/testfs/l1: already migrated via another link
\n\r[K/mnt/testfs/l2: already migrated via another link
:
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is due to incorrect use of &quot;-e&quot; and also passing the &quot;-v&quot; option through to &quot;lfs migrate&quot;, which causes the filename to be printed twice.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
